main event: The witness observed a long white streak in the sky that lasted about 10 seconds, followed by a green glowing object with an erratic bounding motion that settled into a steady glow and traveled west.
interesting points: The first object appeared in the southeast and traveled west to the horizon.
The second object had a greenish tint and was visible for about 4 seconds.
The witness lost the original paper with the information and found it again later.
The Air Force requested the witness complete an additional questionnaire for further analysis and evaluation.
The sighting occurred on October 25, 1959 in Mansfield, Pennsylvania.
sighted object: a long white streak and a green glowing object
